channel.title: CVE Feed for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite

item.title: CVE-2023-32481|2023-07-20T11:26:27.662Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Wyse Management Suite versions prior to 4.0 contain a denial-of-service vulnerability. An authenticated malicious user can flood the configured SMTP server with numerous requests in order to deny access to the system.

item.title: CVE-2023-32482|2023-07-20T11:31:44.188Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Wyse Management Suite versions prior to 4.0 contain an improper authorization vulnerability. An authenticated malicious user with privileged access can push policies to unauthorized tenant group.

item.title: CVE-2023-32483|2023-07-20T11:49:54.416Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Wyse Management Suite versions prior to 4.0 contain a sensitive information disclosure vulnerability. An authenticated malicious user having local access to the system running the application could exploit this vulnerability to read sensitive information written to log files.
